'''Robotrek''' (known as '''Slapstick''' (スラップスティック) in Japan) is an [[action RPG]] developed by [[Quintet]] and published by [[Enix]] for the [[Super Nintendo Entertainment System|Super Nintendo]] in 1994.

== Overview ==

Robotrek is unique among Quintet's games for its lighter, more comedic tone and its innovative robot-building mechanics. The player controls a young inventor who creates robots to fight battles, combining parts and items to create powerful machines.

== Gameplay ==

=== Robot System ===

The player can build and customize up to three robots:
* Each robot has stats: HP, EN (Energy), Power, Guard, Speed
* Robots are built from parts found or purchased
* Parts can be combined to create new inventions
* Robots level up separately from the hero

=== Combat ===

* Turn-based battle system
* Robots fight while the hero provides support
* Energy management is crucial for special attacks
* Multiple robots can be deployed in harder battles

=== Invention System ===

One of Robotrek's unique features:
* Combine items to create new items/equipment
* Secret combinations unlock powerful gear
* The "Invention" machine in each town allows crafting

